Author: cipi#4502
Content:
the most important thing is network connectivity... problem is, that you don't know how good the hoster is beforehand, because most of them don't make their peering partners and network infrastructure public, so you will have to try it out...
i found a very good method to do it, but it takes 1 month till you have the result... and that is: run a tor relay and look what the "advertised bandwith" is after 1 month

Author: NutellaLicka#4241
Content: On that note. Having a node in Australia when everyone else is in the northern hemisphere hurts.

Author: cipi#4502
Content: yes, that is a problem... exactly the problem i have with my AR-node that is located in HongKong... it hardly made it to 7th place last season... my other node (Dallas, USA) is second and the hardware is very similar, even the hoster is the same
